The dimidiate pixel model’s core concept for FVC calculation is based on the assumption that a pixel primarily comprises two components: vegetation and soil. This approach sets NDVI’s upper and lower limits within a 5% confidence interval18, accurately reflecting both elements (FVCmax at 100% for vegetation, FVCmin at 0% for soil), by examining NDVI grayscale variation in the dataset. FVC is then calculated using Eq. (5).5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
